items.name: Status Skull
items.description: This bony little buddy hovers above your head like a morbid halo, letting everyone know that you're not afraid to embrace your dark side

items.name: Feather
items.description: Totally not just bird dandruff. Mix with other junk to make stuff you probably don't need.

items.name: Gold Thread
items.description: Supposedly all the high-rollers love weaving this flashy crap into their threads to scream 'I'm loaded’. Gaudy as hell if you ask me.

items.name: Banana Hat
items.description: Feeling a bit mushy? Then this is the hat for you.

items.name: Dragon Helm
items.description: This bold crimson helmet is the perfect way to make a statement without saying a word. Slay all day!

items.name: Bowl of Soup
items.description: Keep your head warm and your tummy happy with this savory accessory! Just don't be surprised if people try to slurp your new lid.

items.name: Blue Halo
items.description: This halo is the perfect way to show off your saintly side without having to sprout wings. Just be careful, bandits may start attacking if they see you wearing this.

items.name: Purple Flame Hat
items.description: This hat is perfect for those who want to look like they are magical without going full-on wizard

items.name: Salt & Pepper
items.description: Together, they're an unstoppable force, ready to tackle any gastronomic challenge. Just remember, a little goes a long way - unless you're a fan of hypertension or sneezing fits.

items.name: Lighter
items.description: Your pocket-sized portal to the primal power of fire. Need to ignite a candle, start a campfire, or dramatically punctuate a point during a heated debate? This little guy has got your back.

items.name: Soup Can
items.description: A cylindrical vessel containing a mysterious liquid that may or may not be edible.

items.name: Banana
items.description: Craft it into something a-peeling.

items.name: Raw Moonstone
items.description: So our shady geological guy swears he sourced these glowing fragments "legally" during a late night mining op ...suuure, Keith 🙄. Anyway, keep this on the DL in case the feds start sniffing around askin' questions about missing moon matter.

items.name: Polished Moonstone
items.description: So Keith claims these smoothed-out space nuggets come "legit" too, but the precise laser-scoring seems suspicious right? Either way, our crafting team swears by these fragments.

items.name: Wooden Log
items.description: A specimen of nature's finest lumber, hand-picked by our team of bark whisperers

items.name: Fries Hat
items.description: Instantly turns you into everyone's favorite side dish. May attract people saying “You gonna eat that?”

items.name: Burger Hat
items.description: Your noggin’s deluxe fast-food fantasy. It's like your head decided to supersize itself. Instantly transforms you from average Joe to walking menu item.

items.name: Mermaid Tiara
items.description: Your ticket to underwater royalty, no gills required. Beach hair not included, but the attitude? That's all you, fish face.

items.name: Safari Hat
items.description: Indiana Jones meets your grandpa's gardening phase. Repels sun and makes you feel way more outdoorsy than you actually are.

items.name: Floppy Sun Hat
items.description: Your head's personal sunshade and portable picnic vibe. It's like SPF 50 meets farmcore fashion.

items.name: Fruit Hat
items.description: It's what happens when fashion raids the fridge. Perfect for those "I woke up like this" days, if you sleep in a fruit salad.

items.name: Sparkler
items.description: It’s Uncle Sam crossed with a lightning bug on your head. Guaranteed to make you the embodiment of "ooh" and "ahh.”

items.name: 4th Firework Hat
items.description: Warning: may cause sudden urges to shout "ooh" and "aah" at yourself. Not recommended for low ceilings or hair gel enthusiasts.

items.name: Ice Cream Hat
items.description: Guaranteed to make people stare - in envy or confusion, we're not sure.

items.name: Flamingo Hat
items.description: Your head’s ticket to fabulous. Warning: may cause sudden urges to stand on one leg. Instant conversation starter or a great excuse to leave parties early.

items.name: Tiki Drink
items.description: Tropical vacation in a glass. Paper umbrella's not just for show - it's keeping your worries from floating to the top.

items.name: Coconut Drink
items.description: Vacation in a shell. Tropical escape meets nature's cup. Palm tree vibes guaranteed.

items.name: Empty Coconut
items.description: Nature's original zero-waste cup. Once full of tropical goodness, now a blank canvas.

items.name: Sliced Coconut
items.description: Perfect for snacking or fooling yourself that your oatmeal is exotic.

items.name: Corn on the Cob
items.description: Nature's typewriter for your teeth. Butter's best friend and floss's worst enemy. May temporarily transform you into a human wood-chipper.

items.name: Watermelon Slice
items.description: Nature's juice box. Handle included.

items.name: Ice Cream
items.description: Just remember: brain freeze is temporary, but these flavor memories? They're forever, baby.

items.name: Strawberry Milk Carton
items.description: It’s as if a fruit basket had a wild party in your mouth. Udderly irresistible.

items.name: Fruit Bowl
items.description: A delicious mish mash of all your favorite fruits, all perfectly ripe!

items.name: Pineapple
items.description: This spiky fruit is perfect for a warm day and was picked at the peak of pine-fection!

items.name: Kiwi Fruit
items.description: Unsuspecting from the outside, but this green fruit is bursting with flavor.. don't worry about all the seeds, those are edible too!

items.name: Swimmers Goggles
items.description: A perfect place to wear them is right on top of your head. What? You have plans to go swimming any time soon?

items.name: Hot Dog Hat
items.description: Perfect for those who relish attention. (Ketchup and mustard not included)

items.name: Chicken Leg
items.description: A well deserved, perfectly cooked, finger licking good chicken leg.

items.name: Earthworm
items.description: They say that the early bird gets the worm... What does that make you?

items.name: P?t Ch?ck?n
items.description: He may be following you around soon...

items.name: Polished Purple Gem
items.description: The dark aura around this purple gem has been enhanced by the polish, but its intentions still aren’t clear.

items.name: Orange Starfish
items.description: This fiery fella wants to be as close to you as possible. We don’t think it's poisonous at all, but we don’t know.

items.name: Blue Starfish
items.description: This cute fella wants to be as close to you as possible. Is it malicious? We don’t know. All we know is that he's blue and he’s kinda cute.

items.name: Cup o' Cola
items.description: This is just your standard cup of cola. Very fizzy, never out of place in any social setting, and not sugar free but sugar full!

items.name: Protective Helmet
items.description: Hard at work or hardly working? Either way, throw this on.

items.name: Blue Eye
items.description: You get the feeling you're being watched by a darting blue eye. We’ve got our eyes on you, but you’ve got your eye on everything else.

items.name: Choco De-Lite
items.description: Crispy chocolate shell, with a cold vanilla ice cream. You can even taste the wooden stick in the middle!

items.name: Dream Pop
items.description: A beautiful swirly popsicle with strawberry on top, and blueberry on the bottom. Beautifully tart and still the perfect amount of sweetness.

items.name: Pink Nautilus Shell
items.description: Found deep on the sea floor, abandoned by its previous owner and ripe for the picking. Where do these things even come from?

items.name: Earth Shard
items.description: These may look like and emerald, or a crystal of some sort, but this shard was taken deep from the center of the earth ( or as close as we could get anyway!)

items.name: Expert Potion Bottle
items.description: This potion bottles are sought out and often out of stock at other retailers, but we may have a monopoly around them. Shhhh, don’t tell anyone.

items.name: Magenta Potion (adv.)
items.description: Crafting this advanced potion shows that you truly understand the art of alchemy. This magenta potion has a faint aroma it smells of colors and looks of flavor.

items.name: Orange Potion (adv.)
items.description: Crafting this advanced potion shows that you truly understand the art of alchemy. This orange potion has a pumpkin and sparkly aroma.

items.name: Orange Potion (beg.)
items.description: This simplistic potion looks a bit watered down and appears to have some additives, however it has an orange color that makes the owner proud.

items.name: Magenta Potion (beg.)
items.description: This simplistic potion looks a bit watered down and appears to have some additives, however it has an deep magenta color that makes the owner proud.

items.name: Pastel Shard
items.description: A huge singular shard broken off a larger cluster, and polished to a shop keep's perfection. Useful for alchemy, glass adjacent items and many more magical purposes.

items.name: Pastel Cluster
items.description: A rough and unpolished cluster. You can see the pastel pearlescent sheen shine through in the perfect light, but it could be way more presentable.

items.name: Rabbit Plush Mask
items.description: Super soft, comfy, lightweight and breathable. It may or may have not been ripped from a child’s plush.

items.name: Brown Rabbit Mask
items.description: Super soft, comfy, lightweight and breathable. It may or may have not been ripped from a child’s hands and dipped in chocolate milk.

items.name: Perfect Pyramid
items.description: You think you can see the future in this thing? We don’t know for sure but there’s something in there, and its more than just a rainbow and light, but that’s all we’ll tell you.

items.name: Towering Black Hat
items.description: This super huge hat ( possibly a repurposed witch’s hat?) towers over you and looks like its about to fall over.

items.name: Helmet DM
items.description: This is just one of the haunted helmet’s we’ve found scattered across the battlegrounds of the internet. This dark magenta helm carries weird spiritual energy.

items.name: MP3 Player
items.description: Jam packed and loaded with your favorite tunes. We snuck into the factory and made sure it had a little bit of everything for everyone.

items.name: Thermometer
items.description: A non-mercury, food safe thermometer, perfect for cooking or distinct alchemy.

items.name: Carrot Sprout
items.description: It’s been 6 weeks since you checked out or watered your carrots, and somehow, one huge sprout is almost ready to be harvested, but the rest are sadly dead.

items.name: SuperStarFish Orange
items.description: This weird genetic mutation of a starfish popped out of the ocean walking on all 5’s. It’s orange color is probably responsible for its survival.

items.name: SuperStarFish Blue
items.description: This weird genetic mutation of a starfish popped out of the ocean crawling on all 5’s. It’s dark blue color is probably responsible for its survival, as it looks like a natural predator.

items.name: Purple Space Mask (L.)
items.description: One of Nova’s specialty recipes, given directly to you. Not available for sale anywhere! a Light metal base to reflect sun away from you.

items.name: Purple Space Mask (D.)
items.description: One of Nova’s specialty recipes, given directly to you. Not available for sale anywhere! a dark metal base to keep you insulated when your far from the sun.

items.name: Counterfeit Permit 1
items.description: This permit looks vaguely like the ones that have been distributed. If you look up close you can tell this was a shoddy job.

items.name: EarBudz
items.description: No wires, no worries. Ignore real-world notifications. Shhh, you're "in a meeting.”

items.name: Basic Crystal Ball
items.description: Peer into the swirling mists of this budget-friendly fortune teller! Disclaimer: May predict your future as "buffering" or "ad 1 of 5." Not our fault—blame those streaming sites!

items.name: Green Scale
items.description: Legend has it that crafty internet surfers use these to blend in with the vast ocean of web pages, dodging those pesky targeted ads like a pro.

items.name: Pink Scale
items.description: A glimmering gem from the digital deep! Just don't hoard too many—your avatar might start smelling fishy.

items.name: Mint Ice Cream Hat
items.description: Rex's creations usually are pretty... interesting. This mint chocolate chip ice cream hat is no different.

items.name: Blue Glowstick
items.description: It has a little bit of its shine left, but you can tell its been through some parties.

items.name: 2000's CD
items.description: Pump up the jam with this relic of the past. ( Ok its not really a relic, but when’s the last time you put one of these on?)

items.name: Water Shard
items.description: Whenever you touch this water shard, it starts to turn back into its natural liquid state. Its better to look and not to touch.

items.name: Fire Shard
items.description: This shard is still hot to the touch. Taken deep from the fiery magma of an undisclosed location, this will imbue a certain elemental fire to your recipes

items.name: Peach
items.description: This peach was so ripe it fell right off the tree!

items.name: Holographic Leaf
items.description: A leaf with such a beautiful reflective sheen that makes it look like it’s straight out of a fairy tale.

items.name: Time-Warped Acorn
items.description: This is the first part of the holographic tree’s life cycle. For some reason, scientists everywhere haven’t been able to find when this item is from

items.name: Hazmask
items.description: While this mask won’t cure you of your ailments, it can be used as a preventative measure to stop any antigens from coming in.

items.name: Slime Green Hat
items.description: This looks like it was once a normal hat. Now its covered in bugs? Maybe cave slime?

items.name: J1mbo's Santa Cap
items.description: The holidays only come once a year (or do they?). Take a seat on Sa1nt N1ck's lap and tell him everything you want for this “holiday” season.

items.name: Farmer J1m's Hat
items.description: Farming runs got you down? Pop on this stylish farmer hat and let the world know that you're on a crop run!

items.name: Shiny Glasses
items.description: I think I can see my reflection in these things! Is that J1mbo or is that Gary Gilbert?? Who’s to say really.

items.name: Purple Heandant
items.description: Its purple and its a pendant.. that goes on your head… get it??

items.name: Gary's Grog
items.description: Consuming this special grog gets you a special role in the J1mmy’s Basement discord.

items.name: Tribal Mask
items.description: Ancient face-tech for the modern pixel warrior! Rumor has it this mask grants +5 to woodcutting and a sudden urge to fletch.

items.name: Twisted Branch
items.description: This branch looks like it came off a thorny tropical tree, but we're not botanists, so who knows.

items.name: Tattered Canvas
items.description: This bolt of canvas appears to be old and ancient, and not in a valuable or pleasing way.

items.name: White Dye Powder
items.description: This is the color of snow, the essence of a cloud, the very being of a glacier.

items.name: Dragonforce Mask
items.description: Epic face mask forged in the fires of dragons. Grants +100 to agility, so don't be surprised if your typing suddenly hits 1000 WPM.

items.name: Elder Hat
items.description: Ancient headwear of wisdom (and questionable fashion choices). Grants +5 to lawn-protection skills and the power to ramble about "the good old days of dial-up.”

items.name: Battery
items.description: Imagine having the power of Zeus in your pocket… Yeah… Pretty intense right?

items.name: Blue Save File
items.description: Our buddy Clippy snagged this from his last job.

items.name: Microchip
items.description: The processing power of the Moon landing almost 60 years ago, all in a nice handheld package.

items.name: Old CRT
items.description: People from retro game tournaments haul these all over the world. Sometimes 4k resolution and max refresh rate is NOT ideal for gaming.

items.name: ERR Screen
items.description: Everything is plugged in, turned on and configured… Right? It’s still not working for some reason and I don’t think this is the BIOS ?

items.name: Tech Blueprints
items.description: This blue paper has a diagram of bits and bots and chips and stuff of that nature. None of it makes any sense, it might as well be in a different language.

items.name: Broken Tower
items.description: Ok, first the error screen and. now this? What isn’t plugged in right? Oh wait, is it plugged in? Does the outlet have any power?

items.name: Basic Computer
items.description: Ok FINALLY! It boots up and everything but for some reason it only has paint, notes, and pinball? why can’t I get anything cool on here.

items.name: GameChip
items.description: Access to any game in the palm of your hands. I wonder if I can hook this into something else?

items.name: Complete Computer
items.description: Full of RGB this bad boy is future proofed for the next 5 years at LEAST. The specs on this thing are through the roof. I wonder if i can finally play flight simulator on this thing?

items.name: Candy Corn
items.description: A handful of triangular treats that whisper sweet nothings... or are they ancient curses?

items.name: Wicked Horns
items.description: Curved and sharp, these horns pulse with an otherworldly energy. Are they a costume piece or a gateway to demonic power? (Made by User: Jesus)

items.name: Ratty Plush
items.description: This adorable stuffed rat has suspiciously realistic eyes that seem to follow you. At night, you swear you hear tiny footsteps… (Made by User: Jesus)

items.name: Glowing Tombstone
items.description: A miniature gravestone that emits an eerie light. The inscription changes when you're not looking.

items.name: Grotesque Skull
items.description: A twisted face frozen in a perpetual scream. Wear at your own risk – it might not want to come off.

items.name: Lavahat
items.description: A cap that bubbles and flows like molten rock. Surprisingly cool to the touch, but leaves ashy residue wherever you go.

items.name: Gentlemans Topper
items.description: A dapper top hat with impeccable manners. It tips itself to passersby, even when you're not wearing it.

items.name: Loose Brain Trucker
items.description: This cap holds more than just your head – a squishy pink brain peeks out from under the brim. It occasionally throbs with brilliant ideas.

items.name: Black Cat Beanie
items.description: A cozy hat with fuzzy cat ears. Wear it on Friday the 13th, and you might find yourself with unexpected feline abilities.

items.name: Haunted Mask
items.description: A sinister visage forged from dark metal, its surface rippling with shadowy tendrils. When worn, whispers of forgotten souls echo in your ears, and your own shadow seems to move of its own accord.

items.name: Dusty Hat
items.description: This hat is filled to the brim with dust.

items.name: Frankie
items.description: Frank is just a big, mismatched softie with bolts for bling who gives clumsy bear hugs and loves poetry, even though his smile comes out more like an adorable grimace.

items.name: Lil Reaper
items.description: A freaky little fella to hang on top of your head. He may or may not be stealing a little of your life energy.

items.name: Silver Faceguard
items.description: A beautifully crafted faceguard made of the finest metal, and a tinge of blood.

items.name: Mini Mole
items.description: A 1 : 100 exact replica of a giant mole! This little guy fits snug on your head and will never slip off.

items.name: Blue Cape
items.description: A thick blue cape procured from the finest haberdashery.

items.name: Tortuous Ornament
items.description: An immense pressure of torture emanates from this ornament.

items.name: Dark Faceguard
items.description: An absurdly dark force is coming from this faceguard. Made of metals never before seen, and worn by old, but not forgiving lords.

items.name: Shaker Bottle
items.description: Therese a little ball in here that makes a rattling sound when shaken.. Oh wait! I think its blending!

items.name: Stuffed Cookie
items.description: A blend of chocolate with a tasty vanilla icing in the middle!

items.name: Idyl's Shake
items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 15% off your order!

items.name: Idyl's Supreme Shake
items.description: You got a complete supreme meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 20% off your order!

items.name: Dr. Swellman's Shake
items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 15% off your order!

items.name: Dr. Swellman's Supreme Shake
items.description: You got a complete supreme meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 20% off your order!

items.name: Reindeer Antlers 2.0
items.description: The classic Christmas headband got an RGB upgrade. Now with 100% more jingle.

items.name: Snowman Plushie
items.description: A cozy snowman plush who decided death-by-melting wasn't his aesthetic. Living his best afterlife as premium headwear.

items.name: Holly Hairclip
items.description: The minimalist's answer to holiday headwear. Perfect for those "I'm festive but professional" meetings.

items.name: Holiday Lights Crown
items.description: When you want to be the human equivalent of holiday cheer. Battery life not included.

items.name: North Pole
items.description: First place in the "Most Extra Holiday Accessory" category. Way more reliable than your phone's GPS (but only points to candy canes and cookie shops).

items.name: Snowglobe Hat
items.description: Your very own portable blizzard. Perfect for those "I wish it would snow" moments during global warming.

items.name: Gingerbread Plushie
items.description: A cozy plush gingerbread friend who volunteered to be a hat. Somehow both adorable and mildly concerning.

items.name: Nutcracker Plushie
items.description: A regal plush nutcracker who traded in his walnut-crushing career for the cushier job of being a hat.

items.name: Abyssoft's Shake
items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 15% off your order!

items.name: Abyssoft's Supreme Shake
items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 20% off your order!

items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 20% off your order!

items.description: You got a complete meal shake! Go to CTRL’s website below and use [the code] at checkout for 15% off your order!
